F=http://pub98.ezboard.com/bflyfishingarkansasandmissouri.showUserPublicProfile?gid=flyfishar>FlyFishAR</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>ezOP</span><br>  Posts: 434<br> <font color=#000000>(8/13/03 11:31 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub98.ezboard.com/fflyfishingarkansasandmissourifrm14.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=132.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.flyfishingarkansas.com/Photo%20Gallery/tn_j.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Running Water</span><hr size=1> Troy:<br>
<br>
If the generate at noon water won't hit Wildcat till about 5 and Rim at about dark. You can still get in plenty of wade fishing but you have to be willing to drive quite a bit.<br>
<br>
John <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#FFFFFF><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> hauloholic</span><br> <span class=usertitle>Unregistered User</span><br>   <font color=#000000>(8/14/03 4:57 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub98.ezboard.com/fflyfishingarkansasandmissourifrm14.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=132.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Gotcha</span><hr size=1> I see what you mean.  Is it common for them to be so consistent on the time they kick on?  Seems to be real random every time I'm up there...  TAM<!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :rolleyes --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/eyes.gif ALT=":rolleyes"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#F9FBFD><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub98.ezboard.com/bflyfishingarkansasandmissouri.showUserPublicProfile?gid=flyfishar>FlyFishAR</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>ezOP</span><br>  Posts: 445<br> <font color=#000000>(8/14/03 5:40 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub98.ezboard.com/fflyfishingarkansasandmissourifrm14.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=132.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.flyfishingarkansas.com/Photo%20Gallery/tn_j.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Running Water</span><hr size=1> Troy:<br>
<br>
With the exception the easiest way to judge what they will do today is to go by what they did yesterday. You can't really predict way out into the future as to what the water levels will be like. Since they generate more often to curb &quot;peak&quot; power needs one of the most useful gauges is the long range weather forecast. If they are expecting either severely hot or cold weather there is a good chance that they will be generating lots of water. If the weather is predicted to be mild they might not generate at all.<br>
<br>
For long range weather forecasting I use the NOAA website. They give fairly accurate general forecast out to 90 days. They can at least give the weather trends for a given month based on ocean temperatures and jet stream history. If you need the website I can post a link for you here. Being a pilot I am a little more anal about the weather than most. If that bores you to tears ignore this post.  <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
John<br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#FFFFFF><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub98.ezboard.com/bflyfishingarkansasandmissouri.showUserPublicProfile?gid=jimmyt@flyfishingarkansasandmissouri>Jimmy T</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Moderator</span><br>  Posts: 161<br> <font color=#000000>(8/14/03 6:04 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub98.ezboard.com/fflyfishingarkansasandmissourifrm14.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=132.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> .</span><hr size=1> TAM &amp; FlyFishAr,<br>
  Random is the guy who pushes the buttons at the DAM.  Krap Shoot is the part time guy who works weekends.  Mike Deihl is the COO or CEO  of SWPA out of Tulsa, Ok.  Don't know if I got his name right here.<br>
<br>
I fished him on 7-9-03.  He is against Min. flow but might be for other ways of supporting trout populations.  IE: O2 injection.  <br>
<br>
John.  Do you remember the post that Rick Golden alluded to about taking water from different levels of the lake to make for some good DO???  We spoke about this on this day.  He said it was very expensive but not so over the long term.   <br>
<br>
Jimmy T.<br>
<br>
